FT  22 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Pounds 177,000 pay rise for ICI chief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Denys Henderson, chairman of ICI and Zeneca, saw his total pay jump from
Pounds 527,000 to Pounds 704,000 last year. The Pounds 177,000 increase was
largely the result of a Pounds 149,000 bonus linked to the demerger of
Zeneca from ICI and the performance of both companies.
Mr Ronnie Hampel, chief executive of ICI, received a total of between Pounds
475,000 and Pounds 480,000 up from Pounds 350,000-Pounds 355,000. His salary
rose from Pounds 340,840 to Pounds 425,000.
