systems, used a front company to leak technical and financial secrets on
orders, Southwark Crown Court heard.
Mr Trevelyan was convicted on four counts of corruption involving a total of
Pounds 8,652 and one charge of attempted corruption, which could have netted
him Pounds 28,580. He was acquitted on three corruption charges. Sentence
was adjourned until April 22 for reports.
