FT  22 MAR 94 / Bad debts hit profit at Unity Trust
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Unity Trust, Britain's trade union bank, suffered a fall in the size of its
retained profit to Pounds 104,000 last year, compared with Pounds 364,000 in
1992, Robert Taylor writes.
It said yesterday when announcing its results for its tenth year of
operation that the fall was partly because of provision for bad debts and
partly because of investment in new services, particularly pensions.
Operating profit before bad-debt provision and taxation was Pounds 2.3m last
year compared with Pounds 1.7m in 1992. Operating income rose to Pounds
7.18m last year from Pounds 6.08m in 1992. Last year the bank wrote off
Pounds 5.72m of bad debt.
