FT  22 MAR 94 / Peer group gathers to mark anniversaries
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This month sees the 15th anniversary of the fall of James Callaghan's Labour
government. This year is also the anniversary of the longest-serving Labour
peer, Lord Listowel, who served in the wartime coalition government in 1944.
Lord Graham of Edmonton, chief whip in the Lords, invited Labour peers who
had served the Attlee (1945-51), Wilson (1964-70, 1974-76) and Callaghan
(1976-79) governments to assemble for the above photograph.
They were, with one of the posts each held:
