FT  22 MAR 94 / Brazil politician quits after corruption probe
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAO PAULO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
One of the most senior politicians named in an inquiry into corruption in
Brazil's Congress yesterday announced his resignation as a congressman.
Mr Genebaldo Correia, former leader of the Party of the Brazilian Democratic
Movement (PMDB), the country's largest, was one of 18 politicians named in
the investigation's final report, released in January. It alleged a
widespread network of corruption by a government budget committee, which
involved politicians earning fees in return for approving building
contracts.
Further investigations are under way and Congress is expected to vote
whether to expel the 18 in the next few weeks.
