Sir, Taking into account the conditions of the accession of Finland to the
European Union, it is not misplaced to assert that 'Finlandisation' was not
that bad. Our national peculiarity was probably better protected under
Soviet influence than by the treaty of the union. More realistically, we
must accept that an empire has fallen and another is rising. After Sweden
and Russia, now it's the time of Europe.
It is part of Finland's destiny to belong to some empire. Then just don't
call it 'accession', but 'annexation']
Manko Pekkulo,
