FT  19 MAR 94 / Missing persons bureau launched
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The first police national missing persons bureau was launched yesterday at
Scotland Yard. It expects to log details of about 100,000 people a year.
Mr David Veness, Metropolitan Police deputy assistant commissioner, said
most of the missing people would be reunited with relatives very quickly and
only about 1,600 would remain unaccounted for.
